Name: Chromableed Studios
AboutMe:
I'm currently a senior, at a state school, pursuing a technical communications major and minor in computer science. I was first exposed to programming in BASIC on the APPLE II while I was still a grade school student, and have been hooked to various degrees since.

I am currently studying and writing in VB.NET, C#(+XNA), and to a lesser extent C++ and various flavors of HTML and web languages. I've also been reading and hoping to study more about Assembly(intel,arm,6502) and C in order to get a better grasp on low level operations.

I also make a couple of pieces of open source software, for MP3 playlists, and cellphone technicians. Check them out at chroma bleed studios at www.chromableedstudios.com if your bored!
